{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01A4BpCdPQqcXn2gqYWVUZJ5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup:\n- Elasticsearch cluster (es-cluster) is v8.11.1 with TLS and security enabled\n- Data nodes (es-data) are also v8.11.1\n- Monitoring cluster is v7.17.9 without security\n\nI need to add Metricbeat and Filebeat sidecars to each Elasticsearch pod (both es-cluster and es-data statefulsets).\n\nLet me check what version of beats to use and what the monitoring setup needs:\n- Metricbeat 8.x can ship metrics to a remote monitoring cluster\n- Filebeat 8.x can ship logs to a remote monitoring cluster\n\nI'll configure Metricbeat with the elasticsearch-xpack module to collect monitoring data from the main cluster and forward it to the monitoring cluster, and Filebeat with the elasticsearch module to gather and ship logs. The main challenge is handling the TLS connection to the primary ES cluster while the monitoring cluster has no security, plus I need to reference the CA certificate that's stored in the es-http secret.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1605,"cache_read_input_tokens":33941,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1605},"output_tokens":22,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"97d41867-54ae-42ae-847a-7e1d6df6cf1e","uuid":"34b51f61-97f2-403b-b5d6-055b1aa5f67a","request_id":"req_011CcQECzRRSAcdLJdaGMcKz"}
