{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GCsHK9m52EW757i7P89SHL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working correctly. Here's a summary of what was accomplished:\n\n**State verified:**\n- All 5 ES pods (es-cluster-0,1,2 + es-data-0,1) each run 3 containers: `elasticsearch`, `metricbeat`, `filebeat`\n- ES cluster health is **green** (5 nodes, 10 active shards)\n\n**Monitoring data flowing to monitoring cluster:**\n- `.monitoring-es-7-mb-2026.06.25` — 488 docs from all 5 nodes (es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2, es-data-0, es-data-1) via **Metricbeat**\n- `elasticsearch-logs-2026.06.25` — 634 docs from all 5 pods via **Filebeat**\n\n**What was done:**\n\n1. **Created `metricbeat-config` ConfigMap** — Metricbeat 7.17.9 with the `elasticsearch-xpack` module collecting metrics from the local node via HTTPS (using the shared `es-certs` volume for SSL), shipping to `http://monitoring-es-http.monitoring.svc.cluster.local:9200`.\n\n2. **Created `filebeat-config` ConfigMap** — Filebeat 8.11.1 using the `container` input type to read pod logs from a hostPath mount at `/var/log/pods`, shipping to the monitoring cluster. Filebeat 8.x was chosen because containerd uses CRI log format that Filebeat 7.x doesn't parse correctly.\n\n3. **Patched both StatefulSets** (`es-cluster` and `es-data`) via strategic merge patch to add the two sidecars and three new volumes (`metricbeat-config`, `filebeat-config`, `pod-logs` hostPath). Rolling updates completed without cluster disruption."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1374,"cache_read_input_tokens":72857,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1374},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"97d41867-54ae-42ae-847a-7e1